->To install angular 6 needed environment:
1.Nodejs(min 6.0 or above)
2.Npm:(->npm set proxy http://kolla.saisudha:password@gtpproxy.mphasis.com:8080 (or)
        npm set https-proxy http://kolla.saisudha:password@gtpproxy.mphasis.com:8080
       ->npm config set strict-ssl false -g)
3.Angular cli(7.3.8 version):(->npm i -g @angular/cli@7.3.8
                              ->[ng -v] to see installed or not)
4.IDE for code(visual studio code)

->ng --version: for angular cli version information.
->npm -v for version of npm.

->Angular is used for single page applications(SPA).
->Uses typescript or Dart and then converts it into javascript(Transpilation(converting from 1 source code to another)).

->creating project:
  ng new projectname
  ng build
  ng serve --open (or) ng s --o(for executing).
  
->npm i for install
  npm update for updating
  npm u for uninstall
  npm u -g @angular/cli
  npm cache clean
  npm i -g @angular/cli
  npm u package@version
  
->ng g c name for creating a component
